You have just installed the new program foobar manually. This program uses
shared libraries, which are installed to /usr/local/foobar/lib.
What is neccesary to do after the installation so that the libraries can be
used?
Choose the best answer.
Mark question for review    
Restart your computer
run ldconfig ##
edit /etc/ld.so.conf to add the new library path and then run ldconfig
edit /etc/ld.so.conf to add the new library path and then run ld.so
create symbolic links from every library in /usr/local/foobar/lib to /usr/lib 



You want to install the debian package file foobar.deb. This file is located
